SmartSpend – Budget Tracker App (OPSC6311)

Overview
SmartSpend is a mobile Budget Tracker application developed using Kotlin in Android Studio. The app is designed to help users efficiently manage their finances by tracking expenses, setting budget goals, and analysing spending patterns through a structured and user-friendly interface.

This project was developed as part of the OPSC6311 Open Source Coding module (Part 2 – App Prototype Development).

---

Purpose
SmartSpend aims to:
- Enable users to monitor daily spending
- Improve financial discipline through budgeting
- Provide structured expense categorisation
- Offer a simple and intuitive user experience

---

Features (Prototype Implementation)

User Authentication
- User registration with username and password
- Secure login functionality

Category Management
- Create custom categories (e.g. Groceries, Transport, Entertainment)

Expense Tracking
Users can add expense entries including:
- Amount
- Date
- Start Time & End Time
- Description
- Category selection

Receipt Upload
- Optional image attachment (e.g. receipt photo) for each expense

Budget Goals
- Set minimum and maximum monthly spending goals

Expense Viewing
- View all expenses within a selected date range
- Access attached receipt images
- View total spending per category

Local Data Storage
- All data is stored locally using Room Database (SQLite)

